data.name: Creamy Bacon and Egg Carbonara Twist
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and creamy pasta dish with crispy bacon and a hint of garlic, perfect for a comforting meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Cook the spaghetti according to package instructions until al dente.
In a skillet, cook the bacon over medium heat until crispy. Remove from the skillet and chop into pieces.
In the same skillet, add minced garlic and saut√© for about 1 minute until fragrant.
In a bowl, whisk together eggs, grated Parmesan cheese, and heavy cream until well combined.
Once the spaghetti is cooked, reserve 1/2 cup of pasta water, then drain the rest.
Quickly add the hot spaghetti to the skillet with garlic and remove from heat. Pour the egg mixture over the pasta, stirring quickly to create a creamy sauce (the residual heat will cook the eggs).
Add bacon pieces and a splash of reserved pasta water if needed to adjust consistency.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste, and garnish with chopped parsley before serving.
data.detailedName: Creamy Bacon and Egg Carbonara Twist
data.modifiersForBase: Added heavy cream and extra garlic for creaminess and flavor.
